comment:
The weird thing is, these comments sections projects opinions after all the facts and evidences has surfaces. And condemns those like Sharon who gave an opinion without knowing all the facts first, and I think her take, that it takes two to tango is objective enough for someone that didn't even know all the facts yet. Because, like Laurie Holden said in this very video, their personal life is that, personal.

I, myself, felt relieved that, after researching about the case. reading/watching a non-bias sources/videos. I can at least make a conclusion, that the Captain of the Black Pearl might be innocent after all. And reading you guys condemning someone else for having an opinion is really jarring. I get you are showing your support, but can you at least be smart about it?

Personally, I prefer an objective take like that if you want a healthy, objective, and open minded discussion. Not just a 'yes man', someone who only parrots whatever you said and agree with everything, or someone stubbornly thinks they are right and not even open for a discussion.

I think she's probably the main aggressor and thats why people have different stories and experiences with him. 

The thing is, you can take a relatively stable person, stick them in a relationship with a very aggressive, unstable individual, and it can bring out problems the stable individual has. Make them more unbalanced and act out of character. 

What I'm saying is, from what I can see, it's likely they have both put hands on each other. She has probably done it far more, to the point where he lashed out at her a few times. Probably nothing serious, but I bet he's pushed her, something, cause I can tell he's not completely innocent in it.

So ultimately while I support him in this. I hope he's learned that when you date crazy, sometimes, that crazy rubs off on you.

It should never have been "believe all", instead "take them all serious".
